<subSubSection id="C30D68BFFFD9FFC6FF53B2F863F1FD76" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA83B34FFD9FFC6FF53B2F863F1FD76" blockId="34.[151,1437,649,1144]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FF53B2F86315FD1D" bold="true" box="[151,286,649,675]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from 
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FD71B2F86143FD1D" box="[693,840,649,675]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">locus typicus</emphasis>
of the 
<typeStatus id="54AC8596FFD9FFC6FC59B2FB61C6FD1A" box="[925,973,650,676]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus, 
<collectingRegion id="49D3F5D6FFD9FFC6FB10B2F86750FD1D" box="[1236,1371,649,675]" country="Tanzania" name="Kilimanjaro" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kilimanjaro</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FAA0B2F86797FD1D" authority="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts, 2021" authorityName="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts" authorityYear="2021" box="[1380,1436,649,675]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kibo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Kibo</taxonomicName>
volcanic massif. Gender neuter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30D68BFFFD9FFC6FF03B2A06662FBC9" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA83B34FFD9FFC6FF03B2A06662FBC9" blockId="34.[151,1437,649,1144]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FF03B2A063E3FD55" bold="true" box="[199,488,721,747]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis and affinities.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FE34B2A0602DFD55" authority="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts, 2021" authorityName="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts" authorityYear="2021" box="[496,550,721,747]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kibo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FE34B2A0602DFD55" box="[496,550,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kibo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a medium-sized salticid with an oval carapace, high in cephalic part, and a trapezoid eye field with the distance between anterior lateral eyes slightly larger than between the posterior laterals. The chelicera is unidentate, with a big tooth on the retrolateral edge. The 
<typeStatus id="54AC8596FFD9FFC6FC3EB36B6621FC8A" box="[1018,1066,794,820]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
species was formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FF53B34C62F8FCE9" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[151,243,829,855]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pochyta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FF53B34C62F8FCE9" box="[151,243,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Pochyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but pattern of leg I spination is different from that in this genus: there are three pairs of ventral spines on tibia and two pairs on metatarsus, these spines are shorter than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FCB8B31061D3FCC5" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[892,984,865,891]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Pochyta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FCB8B31061D3FCC5" box="[892,984,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Pochyta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FBA6B3106693FCC5" authority="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts, 2021" authorityName="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts" authorityYear="2021" box="[1122,1176,865,891]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kibo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FBA6B3106693FCC5" box="[1122,1176,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kibo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the structure of the genitalia. The male palpal organ has an oval bulb divided by longitudinal fossa into two lobes and a ribbon-like embolus with the base set between these lobes. The epigyne has relatively small spermathecae and membranous seminal ducts. The body proportions and the presence of a tarsal retrolateral spine on the female palp confirm that the genus is related to the other members of the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FC6EB3806644FBB5" authorityName="Bodner &amp; Maddison" authorityYear="2012" box="[938,1103,1009,1035]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Thiratoscirtina">Thiratoscirtina</taxonomicName>
of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FB1CB3806355FB8E" authority="(sensu Maddison 2015 a)" baseAuthorityName="Maddison" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Arachnida" family="Hahniidae" genus="Aelurillini" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Aelurillini (sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8646C5FFD9FFC6FF53B464635DFB8E" author="Maddison, W. P." box="[151,342,1045,1072]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="231 - 292" refId="ref16268" refString="Maddison, W. P. (2015 a) A phylogenetic classification of jumping spiders (Araneae: Salticidae). The Journal of Arachnology, 43 (3), 231 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1636 / arac- 43 - 03 - 231 - 292" type="journal article" year="2015">Maddison 2015a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Thiratoscirtines are a large group of salticids, very diverse in the Afrotropics, and their phylogeny is yet to be applied to morphological characters, homology hypotheses and synapomorphies. The phylogenetic relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1740B7FFD9FFC6FE88B42C6389FBC9" authority="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts, 2021" authorityName="Wesołowska &amp; Szűts" authorityYear="2021" box="[332,386,1117,1143]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Kibo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B963E726FFD9FFC6FE88B42C6389FBC9" box="[332,386,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Kibo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any sequence data is presently difficult even to speculate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
